confirm the size or timing of any such increase, Kuwait's oil
minister, Sheikh Saud Nasser Sabah, said OPEC is likely to raise
its official production by as much as 1.7 million barrels of crude
a day. (Summary from wires.) By Edmund L. Andrews.
