tucked into a crevice a note to God. Then he made the sign of the
cross at the most sacred site in Judaism, and a hush carpeted the
plaza as the moment sunk in. The pope's note bore the message of
reconciliation that has been the public theme of his six-day
personal pilgrimage. By Deborah Sontag and Alessandra Stanley.
