<SLUG> BC-GEN-TV-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHAT'S AHEAD ON TV THIS WEEK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TODAY &QL; 
Just so you know, some of the categories for the questions on the
new Fox cable game show ``Sports Geniuses'' are a little twisted.
Such as: `Who likes Ohio State? The Buckeye do.'' ``Sports
Geniuses,'' Fox Sports Net, 6 and 11 p.m. &QL; 
TUESDAY &QL; 
``You Gotta Have Wa'' is the title for the autobiography of Randy
Bass, the former journeyman major-leaguer who became a baseball
Godzilla in the 1980s when he challenged the single-season Japanese
League home-run record. Although Sammy Sosa and Mike Piazza should
be no threat to defect when the Cubs and Mets travel to Tokyo for
the first overseas opening to the American big-league season,
they've gotta have wallop. In their bats. If only to discourage
more Japanese League pitchers who get the crazy idea of trying
their trickery in the U.S. MLB: Chicago Cubs. vs. New York Mets
from Tokyo, Fox Sports Net, 2 a.m. early Wednesday, replayed
Wednesday at 1 p.m. (Also, FSN has Game 2, early Thursday at 2
a.m., replayed at 1 p.m.) &QL; 
WEDNESDAY &QL; 
A must-win for the Kings, as far as the Ducks are concerned. NHL:
San Jose at Kings, Fox Sports Net, ESPN2, 7 p.m. &QL; 
THURSDAY &QL; 
Aren't you at least curious to see who ends up in the NIT (Not
Interested Tournament) finale? Winning this is like ... nothing we
can even think of, actually. NIT title game, ESPN, 4 p.m. &QL; 
FRIDAY &QL; 
The last face-to-face meeting between NBA-leading-scorer candidates
Shaq and Iverson. In their only other shoot-off, Shaq had the
answer, 22-16. NBA: Philadelphia at Lakers, Fox Sports Net, 7:30
p.m. &QL; 
SATURDAY &QL; 
After further review, UCLA's loss to Iowa State has been overturned
and the Bruins qualify for the Final Four! April Fools', you fool.
NCAA men's Final Four: Channel 2, Wisconsin vs. Michigan State,
2:42 p.m.; North Carolina vs. Florida, 30 minutes after the first
game. &QL; 
SUNDAY &QL; 
Request for Phil Jackson: Please wear a mike so we can hear what
you're muttering about Jeff Van Gundy. NBA: New York at Lakers,
Channel 4, 3:30 p.m. &QL;
</P>
