<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dressed to thrill in Oscar-worthy hues
 &HT;    By Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Oscar fashion took a colorful turn for the better
Sunday night. Many of Hollywood's leading ladies helped enliven the
ceremonies by dressing in a ravishing array of shades.
</P>
<P>
   Down in front! We wonder who had the misfortune of sitting
behind R&AMP;B priestess Erykah Badu. Her green, raffia-wrapped
headpiece was taller than Haley Joel Osment. At least Badu had the
presence of mind to change out of this green leather monstrosity
she designed herself. As an award presenter later she wore a simple
green chiffon gown.
</P>
<P>
   Grape juice: Ashley Judd's purple gown was designed for her by
Valentino; she completed the look to stunning perfection with a
shawl, a hair ornament and eyeshadow to match.
</P>
<P>
   The gold standard: Nicole Kidman's off-the-shoulder gown with
its ruffled hem and neckline gave her a statuesque appearance. And
hubby Tom Cruise gave a nod to old-style movie glamour in his
vintage-look tuxedo and antique white shirt.
</P>
<P>
   Hey, good-lookin': Lucy Liu wore a one-shouldered gown worth
saluting. It sparkled (and clung) in all the right places, yet it
had a demure quality to it that was rare on this night of cleavage
mania.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
