<P>
   UGANDA-CULT-LEADER (Kabumba, Uganda) _ For a man so devoted to
God, the idea must have seemed so right, so real. Three women,
meeting Joseph Kibwetere for the first time, told him that the
Virgin Mary had led them to him and that he had been anointed to
help them spread the word of God. It was, he believed, his reward
for a lifetime of piety and prayer. It was, his family now says,
the beginning of his unrepentant turn away from the faith that had
made him a model man and toward an obsession that would make him a
murderer. By Henri E. Cauvin.
</P>
<P>
   TYRANTS-SWIMMING-POOLS (Istanbul, Turkey) _ When Ethem Erkoc
decided to go into the swimming pool business, he had no idea that
he would one day be known as poolmaker to tyrants. It just turned
out that way. Asked how he assembled his unusual client list, which
includes Saddam Hussein and Moammar Gadhafi, Erkoc said he assumes
that authoritarian leaders chat about things like swimming pools:
``Maybe it's not an official club, but they communicate,'' he said.
``When they get together, one might say to the other, `Nice pool,
who built it for you?''' By Stephen Kinzer.
</P>
