   DIGICOM-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Digital Commerce column: the
focus on money, money, money that we encounter daily in the
Internet economy is almost impossible to discuss rationally in most
quarters. Try telling someone hit by the money truck that the
making of millions overnight does not justify the present means _
like poor business practices, rejection of even sensible government
oversight and early profit-taking. Say that out loud, and you can
live the experience of clearing a room in 10 seconds flat. But it
appears that something is shifting. Venture investors, the fuel of
the Internet economy, have started to question the path that so
many Internet companies have taken _ despite the tremendous profit
they make from the present state of affairs. By Denise Caruso.
