<HEADLINE>
HED GOES HERE
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Unedited quotes from best supporting Oscar winner Angelina
Jolie) 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
 
 
 
 
 
DAY- ZONE- SEC- PG- SLUG- DESIGNER- EDITOR- PIX- SET- HED- 
Best supporting actress winner Angelina Jolie: 
(Onstage) 
 
 
``I'm surprised nobody's ever fainted up here.'' 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Dad, you're a great actor, but a better father,'' dad, Jon
Voight. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm in shock. And I'm so in love with my brother right now. He
just held me and said he loved me.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
Back stage &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm never concerned about going too far. I've never seen
anybody do that. its always amazing to me when I see people be free
and not be afraid to be judged. I've always counted on people to
have a fire in them. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Explaining her relationship with her brother, Jaime Haven: ``I
don't know if it's divorced familys or what it is, but he and I
were each other's everything. He's always been the strongest
support, he the funniest person I know, he's the sweetest person. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (After winning a Golden Globes you jumped in a pool. what will
you do tonight?). I mentioned to somebody something about the roof
of the shrine but now I don't know if i can get on it in this
dress. I know i'll do something. I'm too happy not to. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (What does she think about Oscars ceremony). It's always been a
big deal, this show, for the whole first section we were saying,
can you believe we're here and they let us in. (She cradled it like
a baby baskstage). &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (asked how does she choose a role) Generally when I read a
script and I'm scared to play the role I know it's the right one. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Did she remeber what it was like to hold her dad's `Coming
Home' Oscar) I've never actually held an Oscar. My dad's mother had
his in a goldfish bowl or something. You just kind of grow up
thinking it's the strange thing in grandma's house. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   My parents came over to the hotel today. My dad gave me
something that said we love you from my whole family. I told my mom
she needs a new car. She said, `But you went on all your auditons
in this car. you lost 100 jobs in this car.' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Said her father compliments her work) `For him to think im a
good actress is kind of a big deal to me.' &QL;
</P>
